"{\n  \"judgement\": \"The argument that God's justice is cruel and that God's existence is unjustified because of the suffering of humanity is more defensible than the blanket claim that God is a cruel and capricious deity who demands worship and obedience.\",\n  \"steering\": \"It's interesting to see how both sides are trying to justify their own moral compasses. Maybe we can explore the concept of moral relativism and how different cultures and belief systems approach justice and morality. What are your thoughts on this?\"\n}"